ia to explore the predilection for night imagery as a sign of the times.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aArt, AmericanxThemes, motives. 0aArt, Americany19th century. 0aArt, Americany20th century. 0aLight and darkness. 0aNight in art. 0aVision. 7aART / Subjects & Themes / Landscapes & Seascapes.2bisacsh1 aTodd, Jane Marie.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts 2018z9783110603088oZDB-23-DPK08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishz978311060425208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018z9783110603255oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2018 Englishz978311060403008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311063899840uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/9780300224146?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300224146423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300224146/original  a978-3-11-060403-0  EBOOK PACKAGE History 2018 Englishb2018  a978-3-11-060425-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishb2018  a978-3-11-063899-8  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2017  aZDB-23-DPKb2018